{
  "texts": [
    "Twitter, YouTube, and Red- dit exhibit similar growth rates (α values) and times to reach half of the unique users (β values).",
    "They also have higher Speed Index values with respect to other platforms, indicating faster growth in unique users compared to Instagram and Facebook.",
    "Conversely, Instagram and Facebook demonstrate steeper user growth (higher α values) but require more time to engage half of the unique users (higher β values).",
    "Remarkably, Facebook has the second largest user volume, but a SI lower than all other platforms except Instagram, suggesting that a delayed interest in the user base is independent of the size.",
    "Regarding news articles, we observed a slower spread of information compared to social media platforms."
  ]
}